    • Method Detail

      • getDocBuilder

        public static DocumentBuilder getDocBuilder()
                                     throws ParserConfigurationException
        Gets a DocumentBuilder to parse a XML property list. As DocumentBuilders are not thread-safe a new DocBuilder is generated for each request.
        Returns:
        A new DocBuilder that can parse property lists w/o an internet connection.
        Throws:
        ParserConfigurationException - If a document builder for parsing a XML property list could not be created. This should not occur.

      • parse

        public static NSObject parse(File f)
                      throws ParserConfigurationException,
                             IOException,
                             SAXException,
                             PropertyListFormatException,
                             ParseException
        Parses a XML property list file.
        Parameters:
        f - The XML property list file.
        Returns:
        The root object of the property list. This is usually a {@link NSDictionary} but can also be a {@link NSArray}.
        Throws:
        ParserConfigurationException - If a document builder for parsing a XML property list could not be created. This should not occur.
        IOException - If any IO error occurs while reading the file.
        SAXException - If any parse error occurs.
        PropertyListFormatException - If the given property list has an invalid format.
        ParseException - If a date string could not be parsed.
        See Also:
        DocumentBuilder.parse(java.io.File)

      • parse

        public static NSObject parse(Document doc)
                      throws PropertyListFormatException,
                             IOException,
                             ParseException
        Parses a property list from an XML document.
        Parameters:
        doc - The XML document.
        Returns:
        The root NSObject of the property list contained in the XML document.
        Throws:
        IOException - If any IO error occurs while reading the file.
        PropertyListFormatException - If the given property list has an invalid format.
        ParseException - If a date string could not be parsed.
